parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the 6.0L diesel engine can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine overheats
white smoke comes out of the exhaust
the vehicle loses power
and the engine stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EGR cooler can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine failure, stalling, and loss of power.
symptoms: The engine overheats
white smoke comes out of the exhaust
the vehicle loses power
and the engine stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbocharger can cause the engine to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The turbo hose blows off
the engine loses power
and the vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine failure, stalling, and loss of power.
symptoms: The engine overheats
coolant leaks
and the engine stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear main seal can cause oil leaks, leading to engine failure and stalling.
symptoms: Oil leaks
the engine stalls
and the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front end suspension and steering system can cause the vehicle to shake violently, making it difficult or impossible to control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes violently
the front end of the vehicle starts to shimmy
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel oscillates back and forth
the vehicle is difficult to control
the vehicle swerves all over the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front end shimmy/vibration can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult to maintain control of the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle shakes or vibrates violently when hitting a bump or pothole
especially at high speeds. The steering wheel may oscillate or shimmy
making it difficult to control the vehicle. The vibration can be so severe that it can cause loss of steering control
leading to accidents or near-miss situations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle suspension can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or property damage.
symptoms: The rear axle suspension fails
causing the vehicle to lose control or crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: The engine stalls suddenly without warning
causing the vehicle to lose power and potentially leading to accidents or near-miss situations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission problems can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates or lurches forward
causing the vehicle to lose control or making it difficult to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power without warning, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power without warning
the "tow haul" light comes on
the engine restarts after stalling
black smoke emits from the tailpipe
the wrench symbol warning indicator illuminates on the instrument panel
and the vehicle becomes difficult to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the FICM can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power without warning, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power without warning
the engine restarts after stalling
black smoke emits from the tailpipe
and the vehicle becomes difficult to start.
